        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section id="Introduction" class="ColumnMaxWidth PaddingTopMediumTexts">
            <h2 class="SectionHeadline AmsterdamColor MarginBottomMediumTexts">HR Tech World unveils full agenda for Amsterdam show next month</h2>
            <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">Amsterdam, 6 September, 2017 - <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>HR Tech World</strong></span>, the fastest growing international event on the Future of Work, has announced the <a href="http://www.hrtechcongress.com/amsterdam/agenda">full agenda</a> for its largest show yet at the Amsterdam RAI on 24-25 October, 2017.</p>

            <p>
				HR Tech World returns to Amsterdam to gather the Who's Who of the industry including innovators and thinkers from leading organisations such as <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Airbus, Reddit, Visa, Uber, TomTom, Deutsche Bahn</strong></span> and <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>IBM </strong></span> to share industry knowledge about how new technologies will shape the world of work as we know it.
            </p>
        </section>
        <!-- END Introduction -->
        <!-- Speakers lineup -->
		<section id="SpeakerLineup" class="ColumnMaxWidth PaddingTopMediumTexts">
		   <h2 class="InvisibleHeadline">Speakers</h2>
			<p>
                Unique content will be delivered via +150 sessions and keynotes across 12 stages, including the popular Future of Work, HR Tech and iRecruit main stages. Attendees will hear from inspirational speakers in the vanguard of the Future of Work, including:<br>

<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Arianna Huffington</strong></span>, Founder and CEO of Thrive Global: Redefining Success: The third metric that can benefit your bottom line<br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Nick Bostrom</strong></span>, Founding Director, Future of Humanity Institute: The future of machine intelligence<br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Niklas Östberg</strong></span>, Co-Founder &amp; CEO, Delivery Hero: What it takes to catch a unicorn?<br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Dr. Daniel Thorniley</strong></span>, Leading Global Economist: The end of work as we know it? (The robots are coming to get you!)<br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Corinne Vigreux</strong></span>, Co-founder, TomTom: Reinventing TomTom<br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Panel: Female Founders - Breaking Tech’s Glass Ceiling</strong></span> with <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Urška Sršen</strong></span>, Co-Founder &amp; CPO, <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Bellabeat</strong></span> and <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Ida Tin</strong></span>, Founder &amp; CEO, <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Clue</strong></span><br>
<span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>Peter Hinssen</strong></span>, Chairman and Co-Founder, Nexxwork: Organizations in the day after tomorrow<br>

			</p>

		</section>



        <!--END Speakers lineup -->
      <!-- Event Description -->
      	<section id="EventDescription" class="ColumnMaxWidth PaddingTopMediumTexts">
      <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts"><span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>HR Tech World </strong></span>is proud to be working with global market leaders including SAP SuccessFactors, Workday and Cornerstone, who continue to be major sponsors at the show. Delegates will have a chance to meet Avature, NGA Human Resources, Benify, IBM, Talentsoft, ADP, The Adecco Group and Oracle and many other innovative companies on the show’s Expo Floor.</p>

      <p>The Expo Floor will also feature the <span class="AmsterdamColor"><strong>HR Tech World Startup Zone</strong></span>, a dedicated area where 100+ of the hottest startups in HR Tech (both early and late stage) will showcase their latest products and solutions. The show’s tailored Startup Competition returns once again and allows pre-selected startups to take center stage to deliver powerful pitches. A panel of industry leading judges and investors will then choose a winner out of 5 finalists and award them with EUR 10,000 of sponsorship as a grand prize. Participants also enjoy the opportunity to network with a roster of top investors and venture capitalists from Index Ventures, Eurohold and Talent Tech Labs. </p>
  </section>
      <!--END Event Description -->

