<!--About HR Tech World-->
        <section id="AboutHRTW" class="PaddingTopBigTexts PaddingBottomBigTexts">
            <h2 class="SectionHeadline WhiteColor ColumnMaxWidth MarginBottomMediumTexts">About HR Tech World</h2>
            <p class="WhiteColor ColumnMaxWidth MarginBottomMediumTexts">Founded in 2011, HR Tech World has earned the reputation of producing the fastest growing HR shows in the world. Its event portfolio has shifted the industry on a global scale and ranked it as the largest Corporate HR Network focused on the Future of Work &amp; HR Technology. HR Tech World shows attract the most influential international thought leaders in the space, including the likes of Sir Richard Branson, Arianna Huffington and Gary Vaynerchuk.
</p>
            <p class="WhiteColor ColumnMaxWidth MarginBottomMediumTexts">HR Tech World is having a powerful impact on shaping the Future of Work by unleashing people's potential and revolutionizing organizational culture, blazing the trail for others to follow. Show locations include London, Amsterdam, San Francisco and Paris and welcomed over 10,000 attendees from 120 countries in 2017.
</p>
<p class="WhiteColor ColumnMaxWidth">
 <a href="https://hrtechcongress.com">https://hrtechcongress.com</a>  </p>
        </section>
        <!-- END About HR Tech World -->

  <!-- Press Registration -->
        <section id="PressRegistration" class="ColumnMaxWidth MarginBottomBigTexts">
            <h2 class="InvisibleHeadline">Press Registration</h2>
              <h2 class="MarginTopSmall MarginBottomMedium SectionHeadline AmsterdamColor">Press registration</h2>

			<p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">All press and media representatives who plan to attend HR Tech World in Amsterdam must register their interest in attending the show. The HR Tech World PR team will review registrations received and send notification by email within 5 working days, as to whether attendance is approved.</p>

        <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">Press Passes are free-of-charge to all press/media/ industry analysts/ bloggers with valid and current credentials. Passes provide access to all Keynote and Break-out Sessions, all activities in the HR Tech World Expo, the Conference bag and access to presentations post-event. Press delegates will also have access to the Press Lounge &amp; Workroom.</p>

<p class="LineClass LineTop"></p>
            <p>
			<b>Please note: You will be required to show identification and credentials when you arrive at the Amsterdam RAI.If you have any questions about registration or require assistance, please contact Andi Lustak at andi.lustak@hrn.io</b></p>

 <p class="LineClass LineBottom MarginBottomMediumTexts"></p>
       <button id="Apply4MediaCTA" class="Button AmsterdamButtonInverted AmsterdamButtonInvertedHover pardotTrackClick FormButton" data-form_id="8" data-popup-open="PressReg" onClick="_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'PressPage', 'PopupOpen', 'ApplyNow4Media']);">apply</button>


             <h2 class="InvisibleHeadline">Press FAQS</h2>
             <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">
        <b>Q: How do members of the press qualify for a press pass?</b><br>

A: Reporters, editors and freelance journalists will need to provide proof of the organization they represent and/ or provide a direct link to their latest written article or report, with name included, posted at an editorial or analyst website. The PR Team will not search a website for an article and publication home pages will not be accepted. A direct link is required.</p>

            <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">
       <b>Q: How do industry analysts qualify for a press pass?</b><br>

A: Freelance writers and analysts from recognised publications and organizations must provide both a business card with an analyst house title and a sample of an industry-related report published in the past six months.</p>

             <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">
      <b> Q: Are financial analysts able to obtain a press pass?</b><br>

A: Financial analysts, regardless of editorial assignments, will not be given editorial press passes.</p>

        <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">

<b>Q. Are bloggers able to obtain a press pass?</b><br>

A. Bloggers are subject to the same press registration process as all other media, and registration will be judged individually and based upon the credibility of the blog itself. Bloggers must have covered HR topics for a minimum of three months with a consistent posting rate (at least 2 posts a week). Additional information, such as Technorati ratings and number of hits/page views, will also be taken into consideration.</p>

         <p class="MarginBottomMediumTexts">
 <b>Q: How are pre-show interviews arranged?</b><br>

A: Contact Andi Lustak at andi.lustak@hrn.io to arrange pre-show interviews with speakers and HR Tech World Founder and CEO, Marc Coleman.</p>

        </section>
